I eat here frequently. Usually brunch but on occasion dinner. I love their coconut margarita and pork chops. On my last visit with my cousin we had brunch. The sign outside said sangria & mimosas which normally come in pitchers for 18.00. When went they said bottomless for 25.00 each person for 1.5 hrs. Ok they switched the brunch drinks cool. Our server took the order and never checked on us, the bartender was the one refilling our drinks from the bar. He saw an empty glass and came to refill it.  If we looked like we were looking for the waitress he came and asked if we needed anything. When the bill came We paid splitting down the middle and wrote in a tip. While we were getting our Things to leave the unattractive waitress came and said we didn't leave enough tip. The nerve. She wanted the suggested 18.59. And said we never give her a big tip or the other guy. (Now you will never get one. You don't even wait on us you take the order bring the food and return with the bill sometimes an hour after we finish) She also had the nerve to say next time we come sheis going to add the gratuity to the bill. I said if you are adding it to everyone's bill fine make it policy but you will not just add it to our bill and single us out. The manager/owner is sitting at the bar not saying a thing. I think it was very tacky of her to approach us about her tip. She got 10.00 for doing nothing. She even pointed out the total we spent as if that should grant a higher tip. We had drinks and a brunch meal. I would probably never go again but my daughter likes their sweet potato fries. I'm just going to have to find her another spot that has those. Or I might just go again to see the treatment we get.

Three friends went there for dinner on Friday.  It was happy hour.  We ordered drinks from the manager while pointing to happy hour prices as well as appetizers.  First the third person's appetizer did not come.  We asked for the owner.  The owner told the waiter to tell us that the appetizers were not ordered during happy hour which was an outright lie.  Second, when the bill came and we noticed that we were not charged happy hour drink prices.  We asked to speak to the owner, she refused again to speak with us, sending the waiter to inform us that we did not order general drinks, but we had ordered specific drinks which were higher.  The owner misled us because she could have stated the drinks were not happy hour prices.  I  have no desires ever to eat at that restaurant.
